lesson:
Lesson: Protocol Inheritance
Protocols can inherit from one or more other protocols. A type that conforms to a protocol that inherits from other protocols must satisfy all requirements in the entire inheritance hierarchy.

Core Concepts:
1. Requirements Accumulation: The child protocol includes all methods and properties of the parent.
2. Polymorphism: A type conforming to the child protocol also implicitly conforms to the parent protocol.

Example:
    protocol Drawable { func draw() }
    protocol Scalable: Drawable {
        func scale(by factor: Double)
    }
    // Conforming to Scalable requires implementing both draw() and scale(by:)

Note: Unlike classes, a protocol can inherit from multiple protocols at once.

